title: Corunna soars four spots in AP football poll
text:
Corunna soars four spots in AP football poll Brian Calloway , Lansing State Journal 6:34 a.m. EDT October 20, 2015 Buy Photo Nick Spitzley (9) and Portland remain No. 2 in Division 5 in this week's Associated Press state football poll. (Photo: Kevin W. Fowler / for the Lansing State Journal) Buy Photo 48 CONNECT 18 TWEET LINKEDIN COMMENT EMAIL MORE 
Late heroics from Jerod Fattal and Corey Mort helped the Corunna football team add to its win streak Friday. 
And that victory has helped the Cavaliers continue to move up in the state rankings. 
Corunna was the area's biggest riser this week, climbing four spots to No. 4 in the latest Associated Press state football rankings. 
The Cavaliers' five-game winning streak is the fourth longest among area teams and was made possible by a late comeback. Fattal's 24-yard touchdown pass to Corey Mort with 35 seconds remaining helped Corunna rally to a 35-28 win over Lake Fenton on Friday and earn a share of the GAC Red title. 
Corunna is one of 10 mid-Michigan teams ranked in the top 10 of their division or receiving votes heading into the final week of the regular season. 
Ithaca remained No. 1 in Division 6 and Portland is still No. 2 in Division 5 to lead all ranked area teams. 
DeWitt and Lakewood, which both fell from the ranks of the unbeatens Friday, dropped several spots this week. DeWitt fell six spots to No. 10 in Division 3, while Lakewood dropped five places to No. 7 in Division 4. 
The other area ranked teams are Grand Ledge (No. 7 in Division 1), Lansing Catholic (No. 5 in Division 5), Pewamo-Westphalia (No. 4 in Division 7) and Fowler (No. 9 in Division 8). 
Morrice is receiving votes just outside the top five in the 8-man division.
